title: Pilot
description: Doogie passes one test to get his driver's license, but he must pass another when he treats a critically ill boy.

title: The Ice Queen Cometh
description: Victoria Burke, the hospital's attractive new chief of radiology, wants some of Doogie's genius genes.

title: A Stitch Called Wanda
description: When Wanda's appendix ruptures with her parents out of town, Doogie ignores hospital policy to operate on her. This creates tension with Dr. Canfield as well as Wanda.

title: Frisky Business
description: Fed up with being regarded as a 'nerd' by his peers and as a 'little kid' by his co-workers, Doogie decides to throw a party when his parents go away for the weekend.

title: The Short Goodbye
description: After arguing with his dad about his finances, Doogie decides to go out on his own and rent an apartment. After hearing that a celebrity is staying at the hospital, Vinnie impersonates Doogie to meet her.

title: Simply Irresistible
description: Frustrated with the strict policies, long shifts and stressful atmosphere of Eastman, Doogie gets a lucrative offer from a group of doctors from an upscale Brentwood hospital and seriously considers taking it.

title: Vinnie Video Vici
description: The hospital agrees to let Vinnie film a documentary about Doogie. However, his annoying techniques and intrusive behavior annoy Doogie who must tell a family that their daughter might have cancer.

title: Blood and Remembrance
description: Doogie's busy schedule causes tension in his relationship with Wanda. He then sees an example of love-gone-wrong at the hospital when one of his patients needs a blood transfusion from his estranged wife who is unwilling to oblige unless he signs the divorce papers.

title: She Ain't Heavy, She's My Cousin
description: Doogie fixes Vinnie up with Wanda's cousin who is much larger than everyone expected. At the hospital, Doogie comes across a patient who is obsessed with her appearance.

title: My Old Man and the Sea
description: Doogie's plans to go on a weekend getaway with Wanda are spoiled when he realizes that it's the same weekend as his dad's annual fishing trip. Not wanting to hurt his dad's feelings, he agrees to go.

title: Tonight's the Night
description: Doogie and Wanda, feeling pressured to have sex, make plans to sleep together when Doogie's parents go away for the weekend. At the hospital, Doogie treats a 17-year old girl who gives birth and then abandons the baby on his doorstep.

title: Every Dog Has His Doogie
description: Doogie, upset at the hospital's lack of compassion and adherence to a strict budget, decides to sneak in a dog with a broken leg and operate on it. When he gets caught, his job becomes at risk.

title: Doogie the Red-Nosed Reindeer
description: After being forced to work a shift on Christmas Eve, Doogie fakes sickness to get out of it and go to a party with his friends.

title: Greed Is Good
description: Doogie goes on a game-show for geniuses only to have everyone wanting a piece of the prizes. At the hospital, he treats an ex-boxer with symptoms of glaucoma.

title: Attack of the Green-Eyed Monster
description: Wanda gets upset after Doogie runs into an attractive former patient at the movie theater and he does nothing to resist her flirting. Doogie's parents stop talking to each other over the same issue.

title: It Ain't Over Till Mrs. Howser Sings
description: When Doogie's mom mammogram reveals a lump on her breast that turns out to be benign, she decides that she is going to start living her life to the fullest, which includes singing at a nightclub.

title: Tough Guys Don't Teach
description: As part of a community relations effort by the hospital, Doogie is asked to go to the high school and teach sexual education. On his first day, he is challenged to an after school fight by the captain of the football team.

title: I Never Sold Shower Heads for My Father
description: Vinnie's reluctance to go into the family business creates tension with his father who may need heart surgery.

title: Doogie's Awesome, Excellent Adventure
description: In return for saving the life of the coolest guy in school, Doogie is rewarded by being allowed to hang around with him and his cool friends. With his new found coolness, Doogie neglects Vinnie and disobeys his father.

title: Use a Slurpy, Go to Jail
description: Doogie and Vinnie are held hostage in a convenience store by a gang member.

title: Whose Mid-Life Crisis Is It Anyway?
description: When Doogie's dad begins to feel old and unimportant, he decides to quit his medical practice. Doogie and his mom then decide to gather many of the patients he has helped over the years in hopes of changing his mind.

title: Vinnie's Blind Date
description: Vinnie romances a blind girl that Doogie introduced him to at the hospital. When she gets an operation that will restore her sight, he worries that she will not find him physically attractive.

title: And the Winner Is...
description: When Doogie and Jack hear a rumor that they are neck and neck for Resident of the Year, they both try to gain an advantage by trying to influence the judges which ultimately puts them in awkward positions.

title: Breaking Up Is Hard to Doogie
description: Realizing that his relationship with Wanda has stalled, Doogie ponders whether to break it off or keep it going and risk being unhappy. Jack gets jealous when Curly begins dating a hotshot doctor.

title: The Grass Ain't Always Greener
description: Fresh off his breakup with Wanda, Doogie scores a date with a Lakers cheerleader. He soon realizes that she is too grown up for him.

title: Frankly, My Dear, I Don't Give a Grand
description: Vinnie comes down with tonsillitis right before he is about to lose his virginity. Doogie is upset with Wanda when she tells him that she will be going away to France for the summer.

title: Doogenstein
description: After having an eerie dream where he is attacked by Frankenstein, Doogie goes to a psychiatrist and realizes that he is missing out on his life because of his job.

title: Guess Who's Coming to Doogie's
description: Doogie is surprised when Raymond, the former gang member who once held him hostage, shows up at the hospital. Impressed by Raymond's transformation into a responsible person, Doogie invites him to dinner and gets him a job at the hospital.

title: Ask Dr. Doogie
description: "Dr. Doogie" becomes an overnight sensation after he appears in public service announcements on a popular music channel. However, when his fame gets in the way of his job and normal life, he must choose whether he wants to keep up the hectic schedule.

title: C'est la Vinnie
description: While trying to talk his pregnant French teacher into helping him improve his failing grade, Vinnie ends up stuck in an elevator with her. She starts to go into labor and he is forced to call Doogie for help.

title: Car Wars
description: Doogie argues with his dad over whether he can buy a 1957 Chevy convertible. At the hospital, Doogie tries to get through to a mentally retarded patient who refuses treatment for a potentially fatal illness.

title: Doogie Sings the Blues
description: Doogie admits a homeless man to the hospital who turns out to be Blind Otis Lemon, a legendary blues player long thought to be dead. When Otis is scheduled for surgery to remove a tumor that could possibly leave him deaf, Vinnie and Raymond sneak him out of the hospital for one last gig.

title: Academia Nuts
description: Doogie is asked to make up an illness for a rich hypochondriac who gives large donations to the hospital. Struggling with his grades, Vinnie decides to drop out of high school.

title: Revenge of the Teenage Dead
description: Vinnie has problems finding someone to play a chainsaw killer in his slasher film. Doogie must spend time with an uptight 13-year old prodigy to determine if he is a good candidate for medical school.

title: Nautilus for Naught
description: Doogie is jealous when Wanda becomes friends with a male nude model in her art class. At the hospital, Doogie suspects that a pretty young model is bulimic. The hospital holds its annual bachelor auction with Doogie participating for the first time.

title: Don't Let the Turkeys Get You Down
description: Vinnie is depressed when he learns that Janine's parents offered her a car if she would break up with him. Katherine's parents come to visit for Thanksgiving which causes tension with David who never felt they accepted him as their son-in-law.

title: Oh Very Young
description: After being dumped by McGuire, Curly starts dating the newly divorced Dr. Canfield. Doogie is chosen as one of five doctors to work with a highly-respected reconstructive surgeon.

title: TV or Not TV
description: Needing a recommendation to get into NYU film school, Vinnie poses as an orderly to try and meet the head of ABC television who is staying at the hospital. Meanwhile, Doogie's first poker night with the guys at the hospital is memorable for all the wrong reasons.

title: A Woman Too Far
description: Doogie is attracted to a nursing student who he asks out behind Wanda's back. A man who is staying at the hospital is married to two different women without each one knowing about the other. He asks Doogie to try and prevent each one from seeing the other.

title: Presumed Guilty
description: When Vinnie takes Doogie's car out for a spin, it gets smashed by a falling piano. Doogie, Vinnie, and Mrs. Howser agree not tell Dr. Howser who secretly finds out via a phone call from the auto mechanic. At the hospital, Doogie tries to order tests for a star college basketball player who refuses to seek treatment for fear that will damage his chances to play professionally.

title: To Live and Die in Brentwood
description: When her mother dies unexpectedly in a car accident, Wanda keeps her distance from Doogie.

title: Air Doogie
description: Doogie, realizing that he has no athletic skills, fakes an injury so he doesn't have to play in an exhibition basketball game against a rival hospital. Raymond tries overly hard to impress a woman staying at the hospital, even though she has no interest in him.

title: A Life in Progress
description: The hospital hires an artist to decorate a mural inside the children's center. When it is found that the artist has AIDS, he is dismissed amid public concerns.

title: My Two Dads
description: Upset that his father won't spend any time with him, Vinnie convinces Doogie and his dad to take them on their annual fishing trip.

title: Nobody Expects the Spanish Inquisition
description: Katherine's parent make a surprise visit to the house while it is being remodeled. Her father quickly makes his presence known by offending the contractor who promptly quits on the spot. At the hospital, Doogie tells a couple with a family history of miscarriages that they're having a baby.

title: Fatal Distraction
description: Still grieving over the death of her mother, Wanda has no time to go out with Doogie. She allows him to go to the hospital's annual Monte Carlo night with someone else. So Doogie asks a student nurse to go as his "date".

title: The Doctor, the Wife, her Son and the Job
description: Doogie's mom takes a job as a patient advocate at the hospital. Doogie, upset because she is causing him embarrassment, and his dad, upset about not having dinner cooked, both think she should quit.

title: Planet of the Dateless
description: Jack comes back from a two-week trip in the Mexican rain forest as a changed man with the hospital no longer part of his plans. Doogie desperately scrambles to get a date for the Eastman dance.

title: Doogie's Wager
description: Vinnie is nervous about possibly not getting accepted into film school. Doogie gets worried when the baby of a couple that has been trying to conceive for 12 years is born premature.

title: A Kiss Ain't Just a Kiss
description: A scorned Janine turns to Doogie. Raymond's estranged father is admitted to the hospital.

title: Dances with Wanda
description: Vinnie and Janine convince Doogie to ask Wanda to the prom. At the hospital, Doogie is amazed by the positive attitude of a girl awaiting a heart transplant.

title: Doogie Has Left the Building: Part 1
Doogie Has Left the Building: Part 2
It's a Damm Shaman
description: Vinnie girlfriend wants to run to Las Vegas to get married. Doogie takes on a curse to save a boys life.

title: Doogstruck
description: Doogie decides to drive to Chicago to see Wanda; Vinnie tags along. But when they reach the desert, the car breaks down. While waiting for it to be fixed, he literally bumps into a woman who gives him a pause to think about what he is doing. And the mechanic shows Vinnie his artistic side.

title: If This Is Adulthood, I'd Rather Be in Philadelphia
What You See Ain't Necessarily What You Get
description: Doogie has an intimate moment with Nurse Spaulding. A arrogant medical student gets under Doogie's skin.

title: There's a Riot Going On
description: April 29, 1992. Doogie, Vinnie and the hospital staff deal with the aftermath of the L.A. Riots.

title: Doogie Doesn't Live Here Anymore
description: When Doogie decides to get his own place, he and his parents go look at some apartments but none of them is to his liking. But when he finds a loft, he feels this is it but his father refuses to support him if he decides to take it.

title: The Patient in Spite of Himself
description: Doogie has to learn how it feels to be a patient. So he checks in and subjected to all the tests that his patients are subjected to.

title: To Err Is Human, to Give Up Isn't a Bad Idea
Do the Right Thing... If You Can Figure Out What It Is
Will the Real Dr. Howser Please Stand Up
description: Doogie and his father disagree on whether a child is a victim of child abuse. Doogie and Vinnie try video dating.

title: The Mother of All Fishing Trips
Roommate with a View
description: Doogie is planning his New Year's celebration. He comes home and finds a girl there. He learns that the man who rented him his place also rented it out to her. They try to live together but the girl is very fancy free which drives the uptight Doogie crazy.

title: It's a Tough Job... But Why Does My Father Have to Do It?
description: Vinnie is upset when his not yet divorced father starts dating another woman. David is offered the position of Head of Family Medicine at the hospital.

title: Love Means Constantly Having to Say You're Sorry
description: After Vinnie loses his virginity to Laura, he feels not good enough for her and begins to behave erratically. Doogie treats a famous actress for a mysterious illness.

title: You've Come a Long Way, Babysitter
Love Makes the World Go 'Round... or Is It Money?
description: A young patient at the hospital develops a crush on Doogie. A computer glitch in Vinnie's bank account gives him $16,000.

title: Dorky Housecall, M.D.
description: Doogie becomes enraged when a newspaper cartoonist, also a patient at the hospital, uses him as a caricature in his comic strip.

title: Eleven Angry People... and Vinnie
description: Vinnie serves on a jury and angers the other jurors by casting the only dissenting vote. Doogie finds out that a well-respected doctor has never gotten his medical license.

title: What Makes Doogie Run
description: Feeling unsatisfied with his position in life, Doogie decides to take acting lessons.
